---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="SocialProof for Handymen — Reviews That Keep Your Schedule Full | SocialProof">
  <main class="for-page">
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="badge">For Handymen</div>
      <h1>Reviews Are the Reason Homeowners Call You — Not Someone Else</h1>
      <p class="subhead">Homeowners won't let a stranger into their house without proof they can trust you. Vouch makes it easy to collect and display testimonials from satisfied customers — so your reputation does the selling before you even pick up the phone.</p>
      <div class="cta-group">
        <a href="https://app.socialproof.dev/signup" class="btn-primary">Start free — no credit card</a>
        <a href="/for" class="btn-secondary">See all industries →</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="pain">
      <h2>Why Handymen Struggle to Get Reviews</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>You do great work, but asking for a review feels awkward when you're packing up your tools</li>
        <li>Customers intend to leave reviews but forget — life moves on</li>
        <li>Google reviews help, but you want testimonials on your own website too</li>
        <li>Without visible reviews, you look just like every other handyman in the area</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="solution">
      <h2>How Vouch Works for Handymen</h2>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Get your collect link</strong> — one permanent link, share it anywhere</li>
        <li><strong>Text it to clients right after the job</strong> — "Thanks for trusting me with your home — would you mind sharing your experience?"</li>
        <li><strong>They fill a quick form</strong> — name, what you fixed, how it went. 60 seconds, no app needed</li>
        <li><strong>Approve and display</strong> — embed on your website with one line of code</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="social-proof-for-sp">
      <h2>What Handymen Say About Vouch</h2>
      <blockquote>
        <p>"I send the link by text when I'm still in the driveway. Half my customers fill it out before I even get home. I've got 30 testimonials now and homeowners mention them when they call to book."</p>
        <cite>— Independent handyman, Denver CO</cite>
      </blockquote>
      <blockquote>
        <p>"I used to rely on word of mouth. Now my website has real testimonials and I rank better on Google too. Best free tool I've added to my business."</p>
        <cite>— Home repair specialist, Phoenix AZ</cite>
      </blockquote>
    </section>

    <section class="use-cases">
      <h2>Works for Every Handyman Setup</h2>
      <div class="grid-3">
        <div class="card"><strong>Solo operators</strong><p>Your reputation IS your business. A library of testimonials on your site works 24/7 to convert site visitors into calls.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><strong>Small handyman crews</strong><p>Collect testimonials across all your technicians. Build a reputation bigger than any one person.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><strong>Multi-trade handymen</strong><p>Display testimonials by service type — plumbing fixes, drywall, painting — to show your range and reliability.</p></div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="faq">
      <h2>Common Questions</h2>
      <details>
        <summary>How do I share the collect link?</summary>
        <p>Text it directly after the job, add it to your invoice, put it on a business card with a QR code, or include it in a follow-up email. The link never changes — set it up once.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Does this replace Google Reviews?</summary>
        <p>No — it complements them. Google Reviews live on Google; Vouch testimonials live on your website. Both matter. Vouch lets you own the experience and display it on your own turf.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What does it cost?</summary>
        <p>Free forever for 1 active widget. No credit card needed. Upgrade to Pro ($19/mo) for multiple widgets and advanced styling.</p>
      </details>
    </section>

    <section class="final-cta">
      <h2>Build the Trust That Keeps Your Schedule Full</h2>
      <p>Set up your testimonial widget in minutes. Free forever for 1 active widget.</p>
      <a href="https://app.socialproof.dev/signup" class="btn-primary">Get started free</a>
    </section>
  </main>

<div class="footer-links" style="margin-top:2rem;padding-top:1.5rem;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:0.9rem;">
